# Beads interchange files are unordered, id-keyed JSONL sets that `bd` re-exports
# (sorted) and reconciles on import by newest `updated_at`. Git's default
# line-merge spuriously conflicts on every divergent commit during a rebase —
# adjacent issue/event insertions overlap even when records are independent.
# The built-in `union` driver concatenates both sides instead of conflicting;
# run `bd import .beads/issues.jsonl` afterward to dedupe any same-id double.
.beads/*.jsonl merge=union
